step_original: Particular provisions: Goods other than those described in Annex XIa (Seafood) of Reg. (EU) 2017/1509
step_description:
You must not import, buy or transfer, directly or indirectly, any of the following from North Korea (DPRK):
- seafood or food containing seafood, including fish, crustaceans, molluscs and other aquatic invertebrates in all forms
- fishing rights
- fish and crustaceans, molluscs and other aquatic invertebrates (CN code 03)
- extracts and juices of fish or crustaceans, molluscs or other aquatic invertebrates (CN code 1603)
- prepared or preserved fish; caviar and caviar substitutes prepared from fish eggs (CN code 1604 )
- crustaceans, molluscs and other aquatic invertebrates, prepared or preserved (CN Code 1605 )
- stuffed pasta, whether or not cooked or otherwise prepared containing more than 20 % by weight of fish, crustaceans, molluscs or other aquatic invertebrate (CN code 1902 20 10)
- Soups and broths and preparations therefor; homogenised composite food preparations, containing fish, crustaceans, molluscs or other aquatic invertebrates (CN code 2104)
If your goods are not described above, you do not need to use this code. Contact the Foreign, Commonwealth and Development Office for further guidance.
